rndStackUnitNumber.description: The unit number (for stackable devices) or 1 for 'stand alone' device.

rndBootPServerAddress.name: rndBootPServerAddress
rndBootPServerAddress.description: The IPAddress of the BOOTP server. the OpenGate will act as a BootP relay if this parameter is not equale to 0.0.0.0.

rndBootPRelaySecThreshold.name: rndBootPRelaySecThreshold
rndBootPRelaySecThreshold.description: BootP requests are relayed only if their SEC field is greater or equal to the threshold value in order to allow local BootP Servers to answer first.

rlBrgMacSwVersion.name: rlBrgMacSwVersion
rlBrgMacSwVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 2.

rlBrgMacSwMaxTableNumber.name: rlBrgMacSwMaxTableNumber
rlBrgMacSwMaxTableNumber.description: Maximum number of MAC Tables supported by the device.

rlBrgMacSwDynamicTables.name: rlBrgMacSwDynamicTables
rlBrgMacSwDynamicTables.description: Specifies whether the device supports port dynamic MAC tables.

rlBrgMacSwOldEntryDeleteMode.name: rlBrgMacSwOldEntryDeleteMode
rlBrgMacSwOldEntryDeleteMode.description: The method used to delete old unused entries refresh_flag: The high level sets a flag when it adds or updates an entry, the Switch clears the flag each time, when it learns the station once more. aging_flag: The high level clears a flag when it adds or updates an entry, the Switch sets the flag each time, when it learns the station once more. aging_time: The high level defines a timeout, the Switch sends a message to the high level each time when the station doesn't send messages during interval between timeout and 2*timeout. Boundaries: The Switch doesn't support any mechanism, and the high level uses two boundaries: red and yellow. When the number of entries exceeds the red boundary, the high level deletes the oldest entries.

rlBrgMacSwSpanningTree.name: rlBrgMacSwSpanningTree
rlBrgMacSwSpanningTree.description: Specifies whether the device supports port the Spanning Tree Protocol.

rlBrgMacSwKeyType.name: rlBrgMacSwKeyType
rlBrgMacSwKeyType.description: Specified the used MAC Address Table kye format: macOnly: One global MAC Address Table per device (leaky VLANs). tagAndMac: MAC Address Table per each VLAN (strick VLANs).

rlBrgMacSwTrapEnable.name: rlBrgMacSwTrapEnable
rlBrgMacSwTrapEnable.description: This variable indicates whether to create a SNMP trap if adding dynamic mac failed due to full hash chain.

rlBrgMacSwOperTrapCount.name: rlBrgMacSwOperTrapCount
rlBrgMacSwOperTrapCount.description: This variable indicates the trap counter status (i.e. number of received MAC addresses since the last trap sent that haven't been inserted into the hash). It is relevant only when trap is enabled.

rlBrgMacSwAdminTrapFrequency.name: rlBrgMacSwAdminTrapFrequency
rlBrgMacSwAdminTrapFrequency.description: This variable indicates the minimal frequency (in seconds) of sending a trap. It is relevant only when trap is enabled.

rlCliMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 1.

rldot1dPriorityMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 1.

rldot1dPriorityPortGroupTable.description: A list of PortGroupNumber for each port.

rldot1dPriorityPortGroupEntry.description: All ports belonging to a same group have the same User Priority to Traffic Class mapping.

rldot1dPriorityPortGroupNumber.name: rldot1dPriorityPortGroupNumber
rldot1dPriorityPortGroupNumber.description: A group, that port belongs to. All ports belonging to a same group have the same User Priority to Traffic Class mapping.

rldot1dStpMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 2.

rldot1dStpType.description: Specifies whether the device supports Spanning Tree per device, or per group.

rldot1dStpEnable.name: rldot1dStpEnable
rldot1dStpEnable.description: Enable / Disable spanning tree. When working in per vlan mode enable / disable STP per all vlans.

rldot1dStpPortMustBelongToVlan.name: rldot1dStpPortMustBelongToVlan
rldot1dStpPortMustBelongToVlan.description: Specifies whether a port must belong to a VLAN in order to participate in the STP.

rldot1dStpExtendedPortNumberFormat.name: rldot1dStpExtendedPortNumberFormat
rldot1dStpExtendedPortNumberFormat.description: Specifies whether the STP uses the extended port fnumber format.

rldot1dStpVlanTable.name: rldot1dStpVlanTable
rldot1dStpVlanTable.description: A table that contains vlan-specific information for the Spanning Tree Protocol.

rldot1dStpVlanEntry.name: rldot1dStpVlanEntry
rldot1dStpVlanEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every Vlan about the Spanning Tree Protocol state for that Vlan.

rldot1dStpVlanEnable.name: rldot1dStpVlanEnable
rldot1dStpVlanEnable.description: Specifies whether this vlan is STP enable or disable

rldot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: rldot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange
rldot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

rldot1dStpTopChanges.name: rldot1dStpTopChanges
rldot1dStpTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

rldot1dStpDesignatedRoot.name: rldot1dStpDesignatedRoot
rldot1dStpDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

rldot1dStpRootCost.name: rldot1dStpRootCost
rldot1dStpRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

rldot1dStpRootPort.name: rldot1dStpRootPort
rldot1dStpRootPort.description: The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge.

rldot1dStpMaxAge.name: rldot1dStpMaxAge
rldot1dStpMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

rldot1dStpHelloTime.name: rldot1dStpHelloTime
rldot1dStpHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

rldot1dStpHoldTime.name: rldot1dStpHoldTime
rldot1dStpHoldTime.description: This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

rldot1dStpForwardDelay.name: rldot1dStpForwardDelay
rldot1dStpForwardDelay.description: This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the Listening and Learning states, which precede the Forwarding state. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database. [Note that this value is the one that this bridge is currently using, in contrast to dot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay which is the value that this bridge and all others would start using if/when this bridge were to become the root.]

rldot1dStpVlanPortTable.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortTable
rldot1dStpVlanPortTable.description: A table that contains pair <vlan, port> specific information for the Spanning Tree Protocol.

rldot1dStpVlanPortEntry.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortEntry
rldot1dStpVlanPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every pair <vlan, port> about the Spanning Tree Protocol state for that pair.

rldot1dStpVlanPortVlan.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortVlan
rldot1dStpVlanPortVlan.description: The Vlan number that the port belongs to, and for which this entry contains Spanning Tree Protocol management information.

rldot1dStpVlanPortPort.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortPort
rldot1dStpVlanPortPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Spanning Tree Protocol management information.

rldot1dStpVlanPortPriority.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortPriority
rldot1dStpVlanPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the more significant 4 bits of the most significant octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of rldot1dStpVlanPort.

rldot1dStpVlanPortState.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortState
rldot1dStpVlanPortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state. For ports which are disabled (see dot1dStpVlanPortEnable), this object will have a value of disabled(1).

rldot1dStpVlanPortEnable.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortEnable
rldot1dStpVlanPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

rldot1dStpVlanPortPathCost.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortPathCost
rldot1dStpVlanPortPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. 802.1D-1990 recommends that the default value of this parameter be in inverse proportion to the speed of the attached LAN.

rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedRoot.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedRoot
rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the Bridge recorded as the Root in the Configuration BPDUs transmitted by the Designated Bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedCost.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedCost
rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedBridge.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedBridge
rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedPort.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedPort
rldot1dStpVlanPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

rldot1dStpVlanPortForwardTransitions.name: rldot1dStpVlanPortForwardTransitions
rldot1dStpVlanPortForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

rldot1dStpTrapVrblifIndex.name: rldot1dStpTrapVrblifIndex
rldot1dStpTrapVrblifIndex.description: The ifIndex of port which STP status was changed

rldot1dStpTrapVrblVID.name: rldot1dStpTrapVrblVID
rldot1dStpTrapVrblVID.description: The VID of VLAN to which the port belongs which STP status was changed

rldot1dStpTypeAfterReset.name: rldot1dStpTypeAfterReset
rldot1dStpTypeAfterReset.description: New mode of spaning tree supported by the device after the next reset.

rldot1dStpMonitorTime.name: rldot1dStpMonitorTime
rldot1dStpMonitorTime.description: Factor of hello-time during which a port is monotored to determine if it is stable.

rldot1dStpBpduCount.name: rldot1dStpBpduCount
rldot1dStpBpduCount.description: The number of bpdu that need to received for the link to be considered stable.

rldot1dStpLastChanged.name: rldot1dStpLastChanged
rldot1dStpLastChanged.description: The last time any object in this table was changed by SNMP or other local management means.

rldot1dStpPortTable.name: rldot1dStpPortTable
rldot1dStpPortTable.description: A table that contains extended pair port specific information.

rldot1dStpPortEntry.name: rldot1dStpPortEntry
rldot1dStpPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port about the Spanning Tree Protocol state for that port.

rldot1dStpPortPort.name: rldot1dStpPortPort
rldot1dStpPortPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Spanning Tree Protocol management information.

rldot1dStpPortDampEnable.name: rldot1dStpPortDampEnable
rldot1dStpPortDampEnable.description: Specified if dampening is enabled on this port.

rldot1dStpPortDampStable.name: rldot1dStpPortDampStable
rldot1dStpPortDampStable.description: Specified if the port is stable.

rldot1dStpPortFilterBpdu.name: rldot1dStpPortFilterBpdu
rldot1dStpPortFilterBpdu.description: Specified if this port should filter bpdus when stp is disabled.

rldot1dStpPortBpduSent.name: rldot1dStpPortBpduSent
rldot1dStpPortBpduSent.description: Specified the number of bpdu sent from this port.

rldot1dStpPortBpduReceived.name: rldot1dStpPortBpduReceived
rldot1dStpPortBpduReceived.description: Specified the number of bpdu received in this port.

rldot1dStpPortRole.name: rldot1dStpPortRole
rldot1dStpPortRole.description: Specified the role of this this port.

rldot1dStpBpduType.name: rldot1dStpBpduType
rldot1dStpBpduType.description: Specified the type of BPDU transmitted by this port.

rldot1dStpPortRestrictedRole.name: rldot1dStpPortRestrictedRole
rldot1dStpPortRestrictedRole.description: If TRUE causes the Port not to be selected as Root Port for the CIST or any MSTI, even if it has the best spanning tree priority vector. Such a Port will be selected as an Alternate Port after the Root Port has been selected.

rldot1dStpPortAutoEdgePort.name: rldot1dStpPortAutoEdgePort
rldot1dStpPortAutoEdgePort.description: If TRUE causes the Port when become up, to enter the blocking state, and if during 3 seconds it doesn't receive a BPDU, it will enter the forwarding state.

rldot1dStpPortLoopback.name: rldot1dStpPortLoopback
rldot1dStpPortLoopback.description: Specified loopback was detected on port.

rldot1dStpPortsEnable.name: rldot1dStpPortsEnable
rldot1dStpPortsEnable.description: Enable / Disable spanning tree on ports by default .

rldot1dStpTaggedFlooding.name: rldot1dStpTaggedFlooding

rldot1dStpPortToDefault.name: rldot1dStpPortToDefault

rldot1dStpSupportedType.name: rldot1dStpSupportedType

rldot1dStpEdgeportSupportInStp.name: rldot1dStpEdgeportSupportInStp
rldot1dStpEdgeportSupportInStp.description: If EdgePort is supported in stpCompatible mode .

rldot1dStpFilterBpdu.name: rldot1dStpFilterBpdu
rldot1dStpFilterBpdu.description: Specified if the device should filter BPDUs when STP is disabled.

rldot1dStpFloodBpduMethod.name: rldot1dStpFloodBpduMethod
rldot1dStpFloodBpduMethod.description: Specified flooding method: 1 - classic - untagged to all stp disabled ports 2 - bridging -normal bridging.

rldot1dStpPortBpduGuardTable.name: rldot1dStpPortBpduGuardTable
rldot1dStpPortBpduGuardTable.description: A table that contains for each port whether it is bpdu guard .

rldot1dStpPortBpduGuardEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port whether it is bpdu guard.

rldot1dStpPortBpduGuardEnable.description: Specified if bpdu guard is enabled on this port.

rldot1dStpSeparatedBridgesEntry.description: Defines the contents of each line in the rlSeparatedBridgesTable table.

rldot1dStpSeparatedBridgesPortEnable.name: rldot1dStpSeparatedBridgesPortEnable
rldot1dStpSeparatedBridgesPortEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the separated bridge feature is enabled on a specified ifIndex.

rldot1dStpSeparatedBridgesAutoConfig.name: rldot1dStpSeparatedBridgesAutoConfig
rldot1dStpSeparatedBridgesAutoConfig.description: Enable / Disable Separated Bridges Automatic Configuration.

rldot1dExtBaseMibVersion.name: rldot1dExtBaseMibVersion
rldot1dExtBaseMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 1.

rldot1sMstpInstanceDesignatedRoot.name: rldot1sMstpInstanceDesignatedRoot
rldot1sMstpInstanceDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Muliple Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

rldot1sMstpInstanceRootCost.name: rldot1sMstpInstanceRootCost
rldot1sMstpInstanceRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

rldot1sMstpInstanceRootPort.name: rldot1sMstpInstanceRootPort
rldot1sMstpInstanceRootPort.description: The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge.

rldot1sMstpInstanceMaxAge.name: rldot1sMstpInstanceMaxAge
rldot1sMstpInstanceMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

rldot1sMstpInstanceHelloTime.name: rldot1sMstpInstanceHelloTime
rldot1sMstpInstanceHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

rldot1sMstpInstanceHoldTime.name: rldot1sMstpInstanceHoldTime
rldot1sMstpInstanceHoldTime.description: This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

rldot1sMstpInstanceForwardDelay.name: rldot1sMstpInstanceForwardDelay
rldot1sMstpInstanceForwardDelay.description: This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the Listening and Learning states, which precede the Forwarding state. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database. [Note that this value is the one that this bridge is currently using, in contrast to dot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay which is the value that this bridge and all others would start using if/when this bridge were to become the root.]

rldot1sMstpInstancePriority.name: rldot1sMstpInstancePriority
rldot1sMstpInstancePriority.description: The value of the write-able portion of the Bridge ID, i.e., the first four bits of the first octet of the (8 octet long) Bridge ID.The value is a product of 4096. The next 12 bit are the msti id . The other (last) 6 octets of the Bridge ID are given by the value of dot1dBaseBridgeAddress.

rldot1sMstpInstanceRemainingHopes.name: rldot1sMstpInstanceRemainingHopes

rldot1sMstpInstancePortPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Spanning Tree Protocol management information.

rldot1sMstpInstancePortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the more significant 4 bits of the most significant octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The value is a product of 16. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of rldot1dStpVlanGroupPort.

rldot1sMstpInstancePortState.name: rldot1sMstpInstancePortState
rldot1sMstpInstancePortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state. For ports which are disabled (see dot1dStpVlanPortEnable), this object will have a value of disabled(1).

rldot1sMstpInstancePortEnable.name: rldot1sMstpInstancePortEnable
rldot1sMstpInstancePortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

rldot1sMstpInstancePortPathCost.name: rldot1sMstpInstancePortPathCost

rldot1sMstpInstancePortDesignatedCost.name: rldot1sMstpInstancePortDesignatedCost
rldot1sMstpInstancePortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

rldot1sMStpInstancePortAdminPathCost.description: The administratively assigned value for the contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root. Writing a value of '0' assigns the automatically calculated default Path Cost value to the port. If the default Path Cost is being used, this object returns '0' when read. Indicates that the Authenticator chose an EAP-method.

rldot1xAuthMultiBackendNonNakResponsesFr.name: rldot1xAuthMultiBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplicant
rldot1xAuthMultiBackendNonNakResponsesFr.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives a response from the Supplicant to an initial EAP-Request, and the response is something other than EAP-NAK (i.e., rxResp becomes TRUE, causing the state machine to transition from REQUEST to RESPONSE, and the response is not an EAP-NAK). Indicates that the Supplicant can respond to the Authenticators chosen EAP-method.

rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthSuccesses.name: rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthSuccesses
rldot1xAuthMultiBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aSuccess becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

rldot1xAuthMultiConfigEntry.description: The configuration information for an Authenticator PAE.

rldot1xAuthMultiControlledPortStatus.description: The current value of the controlled Port status parameter for the Port.

rldot1xBpduFilteringEnabled.description: Specify that when 802.1x is globally disabled, 802.1x BPDU packets would be filtered or bridged.

rndEndOfMib.name: rndEndOfMib
rndEndOfMib.description: This variable indicates this is the end of RND MIB.

rxOverflowHWFault.name: rxOverflowHWFault
rxOverflowHWFault.description: An RX buffer overflow has occurred in one of the LAN or link interfaces. The bound variable rndErrorDesc provides the interface number.

txOverflowHWFault.name: txOverflowHWFault
txOverflowHWFault.description: Interport queue overflow has occurred in one of the LAN or link interfaces. The bound variable rndErrorDesc provides the interface number.

routeTableOverflow.name: routeTableOverflow
routeTableOverflow.description: An overflow condition has occurred in the Routing Table. The Routing Table is used for IP routing algorithm (RIP).

resetRequired.description: This trap indicates that in order to perform the last SET request, a reset operation of the router/bridge is required. endTftp.name: endTftp
endTftp.description: This trap indicates that in the device finished a TFTP transaction with the management station. variable rndErrorDesc and rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

abortTftp.name: abortTftp
abortTftp.description: This trap indicates that in the device aborted a TFTP session with the management station. Variable rndErrorDesc and rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

startTftp.name: startTftp
startTftp.description: Informational trap indicating that the device has intiated a TFTP session. rndErrorDesc will contain the file type in question

faultBackUp.name: faultBackUp
faultBackUp.description: Automantic switchover to backup link because of main link fault.

ipxRipTblOverflow.name: ipxRipTblOverflow
ipxRipTblOverflow.description: This trap indicates that in an OpenGate IPX RIP table overflow. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

ipxSapTblOverflow.name: ipxSapTblOverflow
ipxSapTblOverflow.description: This trap indicates that in an OpenGate IPX SAP table overflow. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity provides the actual message text and severity respectively.

facsAccessVoilation.name: facsAccessVoilation

forwardingTabOverflow.name: forwardingTabOverflow

framRelaySwitchConnectionUp.name: framRelaySwitchConnectionUp
framRelaySwitchConnectionUp.description: This trap indicates that a connection establish between the Frame relay Switch and the WanGate. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== warning )

framRelaySwitchConnectionDown.name: framRelaySwitchConnectionDown
framRelaySwitchConnectionDown.description: This trap indicates that a connection between the Frame Relay Switch and the WanGate failed. The bound variable rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== warning )

rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow.name: rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow
rsIpZhrConnectionsTableOverflow.description: The Zero Hop Routing connections Table has been overflown.

rsIpZhrVirtualIpAsSource.name: rsIpZhrVirtualIpAsSource

pppSecurityViolation.name: pppSecurityViolation
pppSecurityViolation.description: This trap indicates that a PPP link got an unrecognized secret. The bound variables rndErrorDesc, rndErrorSeverity(== warning ), interface Number. and pppSecurityIdentity

rsWSDRedundancySwitch.name: rsWSDRedundancySwitch
rsWSDRedundancySwitch.description: Whenever main server fails and backup takes over or server comes up after failure a trap of this type is issued.

rsDhcpAllocationFailure.name: rsDhcpAllocationFailure
rsDhcpAllocationFailure.description: DHCP failed to allocate an IP address to a requesting host because of memory shortage or inadequate configuration of available IP addresses.
